<p align="left">
In the invoice overview, all invoices are displayed with accompanying information.<br />
<br />
By default, NOT Cancelled entries are displayed. To view other entries, then<br />
please click on the arrow symbols (up = NOT Cancelled, Down = Cancelled, right = Show all).<br />
You can also change the sorted order. Standard Sort by Date (newest entries first).<br />
<br />
If you want to create a new invoice, then please click on New. You get<br />
now to the invoice mask. First, select a customer. After a<br />
customer has been chosen, additional customer information<br />
are indicated (account number, payment method, date, message etc.)<br />
Now you can add to the invoice items, please click on Position / Article - [  New  ],<br />
then click Search. In the Position list select the desired items.<br />
<br />
If you change data such as the date, then it is necessary either the TAB key to<br />
press or to click another field for the changes to be adopted.<br />
After you click Save, the invoice is saved. (Table: invoice and invoicepos).<br />
<br />
If you want to make a payment for an invoice, then please click on the stamp icon.<br />
Or choose from the info page Transaction. This will take you to the payment mask.<br />
<br />
Note:<br />
<br />
Invoices can not be deleted. Invoice can be cancelled from the info page.<br />
(only as long as no payment for the invoice available).<br />
(Administrator and User Group Manager and Root)<br />
